    "He taught as a private lecturer beginning in 1905 at Erlangen University.": [],
    "With the appearance of his 1907 <em>Habilitationschrift</em> concerning an Apollo head, he assumed a Professorship at Erlangen, where he advanced to <em>Ordinarius</em> in 1913.": [],
    "Together with <a href=\"/sievekingj\">Johannes Sieveking</a>, he edited the papers of Furtw\u00e4ngler after Furtw\u00e4ngler's untimely death.": [],
    "After military service during the First World War, Curtius taught at the University of Freiburg im Breisgau, 1918-1920.": [
